name:
Panerai Luminor Submersible 1950 3 Days Automatic
PAM01305
size:
* Matte black dial * The dial index, hands, and bezel at 12 o'clock are equipped with luminova. *The tax-included list price at that time was probably around 1,000,000 to 1,100,000 yen. * Rounded sapphire glass windshield Reverse rotation prevention rotating bezel See-through screw back * 31 jewels Incabloc anti-seismic device Flat hairspring Balance with mean time screw 28,800 vibrations Second hand stopping mechanism With this method, it is possible to move only the short hand without stopping the movement of the second hand, so it is easy to correct the time difference. *PAM01305 was originally a back scale, but after a minor change, it became a normal back cover instead of a back scale. The PAM number is the same as PAM01305, but the OP number is different. There are roughly two types of PAM01305, but I think there are three types if you classify them more finely. The differences are as follows. *Dial notation "LUMINOR (white)" "SUBMERSIBLE (white)" "PANERAI (white)" "Automatic (white)" back scale *Dial notation "LUMINOR (white)" "SUBMERSIBLE (white)" "PANERI (white)" )" "Automatic (white)" normal back cover

Belt: genuine rubber strap / genuine titanium buckle

Accessories: Outer box Inner box Instruction manual Warranty and rate certificate booklet (July 2017 domestic official) Strap replacement tool Driver Replacement leather belt (unused)

Case diameter/arm circumference: 47mm

Condition: *Used A* Relatively clean used item with few small scratches and little feeling of use. *There are no scratches on the sapphire glass windshield. *There is slight corrosion on the index at 6 o'clock on the dial, but I don't think it's noticeable to the naked eye. *The rubber strap shows some usability. The replacement leather belt is unused. *Scratches on the side of the lug in the first and second enlarged images are superficial, and you can hardly feel it getting caught even if you put your fingernail on it. I don't think it matters much when wearing a watch. *In the enlarged image of the dial, you may be able to see something like a scratch around the "N" of the letter "OFFICINE..." on the self-winding rotor, but this is small dust adhering to the glass surface. . Please rest assured that it is actually clean.

* Matte black dial * The dial index, hands, and bezel at 12 o'clock are equipped with luminova. *The tax-included list price at that time was probably around 1,000,000 to 1,100,000 yen. * Rounded sapphire glass windshield Reverse rotation prevention rotating bezel See-through screw back * 31 jewels Incabloc anti-seismic device Flat hairspring Balance with mean time screw 28,800 vibrations Second hand stopping mechanism With this method, it is possible to move only the short hand without stopping the movement of the second hand, so it is easy to correct the time difference. *PAM01305 was originally a back scale, but after a minor change, it became a normal back cover instead of a back scale. The PAM number is the same as PAM01305, but the OP number is different. There are roughly two types of PAM01305, but I think there are three types if you classify them more finely. The differences are as follows. *Dial notation "LUMINOR (white)" "SUBMERSIBLE (white)" "PANERAI (white)" "Automatic (white)" back scale *Dial notation "LUMINOR (white)" "SUBMERSIBLE (white)" "PANERI (white)" )" "Automatic (white)" normal back cover

size:
It was in 1997 that Panerai, which specialized in manufacturing military watches, started selling to the private sector. Panerai's representative model "Luminor" is a reproduction of the former design. This is a new model announced in 2019 with a novel silver dial, and each detail design is alternately polished and satin finished, giving it a sophisticated impression. The completely in-house self-winding P.9010 caliber can move only the hour hand back and forth in one-hour increments, so you can adjust to overseas time without interlocking the minute hand when traveling abroad.

There are some small scratches, but it is in a beautiful state. V number (manufactured around 2019) precision adjustment and exterior finish. *Accessories may have scratches, stains, or deterioration.

Case diameter: 44mm Maximum arm circumference: 19.5cm

name:
Oris Aquis
Ocean Trilogy Set Aquis Great Barrier Reef III Clean Ocean Blue Whale
size:
Oris Ocean Trilogy Set - a limited & numbered edition set of only 200 sets, with all 3 pieces sharing the same limited edition number. The trio of watches includes the: • Oris Blue Whale limited edition 200 pieces, available exclusively as part of the Oris Ocean Trilogy set).

• Oris Great Barrier Reef III limited edition 2000 pieces.

• Oris Clean Ocean limited edition 2000 pieces.

The set is delivered in an exclusive & eye-catching presentation box produced from used plastic bottles. Only chemically inert recycled plastic waste was selected as part of the process. The box is created in 4 steps: • Use plastic bottles are collected.

• The plastic bottles are then shredded into small pieces.

• The pieces are selectively hand arranged & then pressed into a panel. The hand selection & positioning of the various colored bottle makes each panel unique.

• Finally the panels are cut to size & assembled as the outer shell of the Oris Ocean Trilogy presentation box .

Oris Blue Whale 01 743 7734 4185-Set: • Case diameter: 45.50mm

• Case back: Special engraving with Blue Whale image.

• Crown: screw down.

• Bezel: Blue ceramic with diving scale.

• Dial: Gradient blue dial, applied hour markers with luminous fill, hands with luminous fill.

• Water resistance: 500m.

• Features: Chronograph function, small seconds sub-dial at 9 o'clock, date window at 4.30 o'clock.

• Movement: Oris caliber 771 (base SW 510), beats at 28,800 vph, contains 27 jewels & has a power reserve of +/- 48 hours.

Oris Great Barrier Reef III 01 743 7734 4185-Set: • Case diameter: 43.50mm

• Case back: Special engraving with Blue Whale image.

• Crown: screw down.

• Bezel: Blue ceramic with diving scale.

• Dial: Gradient blue dial, applied hour markers with luminous fill, hands with luminous fill.

• Water resistance: 300m.

• Features: Central date indicator hand.

• Movement: Oris caliber 743 (base SW 220-1), beats at 28,800 vph, contains 28 jewels & has a power reserve of +/- 38 hours.

Oris Clean Ocean 01 733 7732 4185-Set: • Case diameter: 39.50mm

• Case back: Special engraving with medallion made of recycled PET plastics set into the case back.

• Crown: screw down.

• Bezel: Blue ceramic with diving scale.

• Dial: Gradient blue dial, applied hour markers with luminous fill, hands with luminous fill.

• Water resistance: 300m.

• Features: Date window at 6 o'clock.

• Movement: Oris caliber 733 (base SW 200-1), beats at 28,800 vph, contains 26 jewels & has a power reserve of +/- 38 hours.
